What you need to know:  In 2020, there were 680 000 Aids-related deaths globally, of which 57 per cent were among men and 43 per cent among women.In Kenya, data from the National Aids & STI Control Programme shared last month shows about five per cent of HIV-positive men on treatment die; for women, those dying account for 2.4 per cent.Studies urge action to challenge the social, cultural and gender norms of manhood that encourage men to take excessive risks, be over-controlling, and view health-seeking behaviours as a sign of weakness.